    "about": "Compound III (Comet) is an EVM-compatible lending protocol that enables users to supply crypto assets as collateral to borrow a single base asset (USDC, USDT, WETH, or USDe depending on market). The protocol uses a monolithic architecture with isolated markets per base asset, each deployed via a transparent upgradeable proxy pattern. Governance is coordinated through COMP token-weighted voting with a Timelock contract. Rewards are distributed to lenders and borrowers via a separate Rewards contract."
